'''Kristijan Jakić''' (born 14 May 1997) is a Croatian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]], and can play as a [[centre-back]] and [[right-back]] for {{German football updater|Augsburg}} club [[FC Augsburg]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

== Club career ==
=== Early career and RNK Split ===
A native of [[Runovići]], Jakić started training at the age of seven at the local {{ill|NK Mračaj Runović|hr}}.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Splitov Jaki iz Runovića: Volim Kaku, beskrajno vjerujem treneru Sabliću|url=http://www.dalmacijanews.hr/clanak/wr87-splitov-jaki-iz-runovica-volim-kaku-beskrajno-vjerujem-treneru-sablicu|website=Dalmacija News|date=5 May 2016|access-date=26 June 2025|language=hr}}</ref> Later, he moved to the nearby [[NK Imotski|Imotski]], spending four seasons<ref>{{Cite web|title=NK Kamen Ivanbegovina: Klub na kojem favoriti "lome zube"|url=http://imotskenovine.hr/nk-kamen-ivanbegovina-klub-kojem-favoriti-lome-zube/|url-status=dead|website=Imotske Novine|date=6 June 2016|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420033232/https://imotskenovine.hr/nk-kamen-ivanbegovina-klub-kojem-favoriti-lome-zube/|archive-date=20 April 2019}}</ref> and qualifying for the [[Croatian Academy Football League]] in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sjajna generacija kadeta NK Imotski, najbolji već prodani u Hajduk i Split|url=http://radioimotski.hr/naslovnica/sjajna-generacija-kadeta-nk-imotski-najbolji-vec-prodani-u-hajduk-i-split/|url-status=dead|publisher=Radio Imotski|date=8 July 2013|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170517170002/http://radioimotski.hr/naslovnica/sjajna-generacija-kadeta-nk-imotski-najbolji-vec-prodani-u-hajduk-i-split/|archive-date=17 May 2017}}</ref> However, Jakić moved to the [[RNK Split]] academy that summer. He debuted for the [[Croatia national under-19 football team|Croatia U19 team]] in 2015<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kristijan Jakić|url=http://hns-cff.hr/players/139876/kristijan-jakic/|url-status=dead|publisher=[[Croatian Football Federation]]|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160404093650/http://hns-cff.hr/players/139876/kristijan-jakic/|archive-date=4 April 2016}}</ref> before moving to RNK Split senior team in a 1–1 home draw against [[NK Osijek|Osijek]], coming as a substitute in the 66th minute for [[Miloš Vidović]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Split vs. Osijek|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/12/20/croatia/1-hnl/nk-split/nk-osijek/2042770/|website=Soccerway|publisher=Platform Group|date=20 December 2015|access-date=26 June 2025}}</ref>

=== Istra 1961 and Lokomotiva ===
In May 2017, following the relegation of RNK Split, Jakić moved to [[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Kristijan Jakić novi je igrač Lokomotive|url=http://www.nklokomotiva.hr/vijest/kristijan-jakic-novi-je-igrac-lokomotive-483|url-status=dead|website=NK Lokomotiva|language=hr|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170620233749/http://www.nklokomotiva.hr/vijest/kristijan-jakic-novi-je-igrac-lokomotive-483|archive-date=20 June 2017}}</ref> After struggling during his first half-season at the club, he requested a loan move to [[NK Istra 1961|Istra 1961]] from club's director of football Božidar Šikić. Jakić spent the second half of the [[2017–18 Croatian First Football League|2017–18 season]] in [[Pula]], where he regained form by Istra coach [[Darko Raić-Sudar]]. He returned to Lokomotiva at the end of the season, where he turned into one of the best players during coach [[Goran Tomić]]'s tenure at the club.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=15 January 2021|title=Novi 'Brozović' otkrio: 'Dinamo je iznad svih u Hrvatskoj, a ja želim dostići vrh i zaigrati u Realu'|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/novi-brozovic-otkrio-dinamo-je-iznad-svih-u-hrvatskoj-a-ja-zelim-dostici-vrh-i-zaigrati-u-realu-15043128|access-date=26 June 2025|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref>

=== Dinamo Zagreb ===
His good performances for Lokomotiva drew attention from Croatian club [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]], who signed him for €1.2 million on 24 July 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|date=24 July 2020|title=Kristijan Jakić potpisao za Dinamo!|url=https://www.gnkdinamo.hr/hr/Novosti/Clanak/kristijan-jakic-potpisao-za-dinamo|access-date=15 January 2021|website=GNK Dinamo Zagreb|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Dobrinić|first=Damir|date=21 October 2020|title=Dinamo napravio 4. najbolji transfer u povijesti i zaradio deset puta više od Hajduka, rekord Lokosa!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/dinamo-napravio-4-najbolji-transfer-u-povijesti-i-zaradio-deset-puta-vise-od-hajduka-rekord-lokosa-15026974|access-date=15 January 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref> Jakić was forced to miss the beginning of the [[2020–21 GNK Dinamo Zagreb season|season]] due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]]. He made his Dinamo debut on 12 September in a 2–1 victory against [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref name=":0" /> In his [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] debut in a goalless draw against [[Feyenoord]] on 22 October, Jakić fouled [[Mark Diemers]] and caused a penalty, which Dinamo goalkeeper [[Dominik Livaković]] saved.<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Lipovac|first1=Nikola|last2=Mršnik|first2=Patrik|date=22 October 2020|title=Totalna ofenziva i drama protiv Feyenoorda: Dinamo s igračem više promašio pobjedu u zadnjim minutama|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/europska-liga/totalna-ofenziva-i-drama-protiv-feyenoorda-dinamo-s-igracem-vise-promasio-pobjedu-u-zadnjim-minutama-15027179|access-date=15 January 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> On 8 November, he scored his first goal for Dinamo Zagreb in a 5–0 victory against Istra 1961.<ref>{{Cite web|date=8 November 2020|title=Razigrani Dinamo, pet golova, Jakić slavi prvijenac|url=https://gnkdinamo.hr/hr/Novosti/Clanak/razigrani-dinamo-pet-golova-jakic-slavi-prvijenac|access-date=15 January 2021|website=GNK Dinamo Zagreb|language=hr}}</ref> By the end of the first half-season, Jakić had already established himself as the important part of Dinamo Zagreb's starting lineup.<ref name=":0" />

On 20 July 2021, in Dinamo Zagreb's [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Q2 CH1.1|Champions League second qualifying round]] against [[AC Omonia|Omonia]], Jakić assisted [[Lovro Majer]] and scored himself as Dinamo Zagreb won 2–0.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Tolić|first=Josip|date=20 July 2021|title=Majer: Ma ovo bismo potpisali; Jakić: Teren baš nije kako treba|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/majer-ma-ovo-bismo-potpisali-jakic-teren-bas-nije-kako-treba-774836|access-date=27 August 2021|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref> Ahead of Dinamo Zagreb's [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#PO CH4.2|Champions League play-off]] against [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol|Sheriff Tiraspol]] on 25 August, Jakić was dropped from the squad, with coach [[Damir Krznar]] claiming he had injured his ankle in the 1–0 [[2021–22 Croatian First Football League|league]] victory over Lokomotiva the weekend before.<ref>{{Cite web|date=24 August 2021|title=Novi problemi u kadru Dinama uoči uzvrata sa Šerifom, ali Krznar ostaje optimist: "Možemo do Lige prvaka!"|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/novi-problemi-u-kadru-dinama-uoci-uzvrata-sa-serifom-ali-krznar-ostaje-optimist-mozemo-do-lige-prvaka---664062.html|access-date=27 August 2021|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref> However, ''[[Sportske novosti]]'' published that Jakić was removed from the squad as a disciplinary measure after he was dissatisfied by the club refusing [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]'s offer to buy him.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Ničota|first=Tomo|date=24 August 2021|title=Pomutnja u Dinamu: Prvotimac poručio da želi transfer i razljutio Krznara koji ga stavlja na 'led'!?|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/liga-prvaka/pomutnja-u-dinamu-prvotimac-porucio-da-zeli-transfer-i-razljutio-krznara-koji-ga-stavlja-na-led-15097198|access-date=27 August 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref> He was unexpectedly named in the starting lineup in the 29 August league derby against [[NK Osijek|Osijek]], and scored the opener as Dinamo won 2–0.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Đukarić|first=Gradimir|date=29 August 2021|title=Video: Slavlje Dinama u Osijeku! Jakić se oprostio pogotkom, Livaković obranio penal, nesretni autogol...|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/video-slavlje-dinama-u-osijeku-jakic-se-oprostio-pogotkom-livakovic-obranio-penal-nesretni-autogol-15098324|access-date=30 August 2021|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr}}</ref>

=== Eintracht Frankfurt ===
On 30 August 2021, Jakić officially moved to German [[Bundesliga]] side [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] on loan with an option to buy at the end of the [[2021–22 Eintracht Frankfurt season|season]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=30 August 2021 |title=Eintracht verpflichtet Kristijan Jakic |url=https://profis.eintracht.de/news/eintracht-verpflichtet-kristijan-jakic-135211/ |access-date=26 June 2025|website=[[Eintracht Frankfurt]] |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=30 August 2021 |title=Kristijan Jakić potpisao za Eintracht, iz kluba oduševljeni: 'Dobili smo igrača kakvog još nismo imali' |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/bundesliga/kristijan-jakic-potpisao-za-eintracht-iz-kluba-odusevljeni-dobili-smo-igraca-kakvog-jos-nismo-imali-15098612 |access-date=30 August 2021 |website=[[Sportske novosti]] |language=hr}}</ref> He made his debut on 12 September in a 1–1 draw against [[VfB Stuttgart]], coming off the bench for [[Ajdin Hrustic|Ajdin Hrustić]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Korać|first=Branimir|date=13 September 2021|title=Jakić debitirao u susretu protiv Sose, Hertha odnijela pobjedu iz Bochuma|url=https://sportnet.rtl.hr/vijesti/554761/nogomet-njemacka/jakic-debitirao-u-susretu-protiv-sose-hertha-odnijela-pobjedu-iz-bochuma/|access-date=16 September 2021|website=Sportnet Croatia|language=hr|archive-date=16 September 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210916211646/https://sportnet.rtl.hr/vijesti/554761/nogomet-njemacka/jakic-debitirao-u-susretu-protiv-sose-hertha-odnijela-pobjedu-iz-bochuma/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Eintracht on 12 December in a 5–2 victory against [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=12 December 2021 |title=Video: Fantastičan prvijenac Jakića: Golman je mogao samo pogledom ispratiti let lopte |url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/video-caleta-car-zabio-u-slavlju-marseillea-protiv-strasbourga-802804 |access-date=12 December 2021 |website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|agency=[[Croatian News Agency]]|language=hr}}</ref> Despite Eintracht Frankfurt's underwhelming performance in [[2021–22 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] where they finished eleventh, Jakić helped the club reach the [[2022 UEFA Europa League Final|Europa League final]] unbeaten, eliminating [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in the process,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Franičević |first=Aldo |date=17 May 2022 |title=Sve što trebate znati o finalu Europske lige između Eintrachta i Rangersa: Nitko ih nije očekivao, a sada u... |url=https://www.rtl.hr/sport/nogomet/sve-sto-trebate-znati-o-finalu-europske-lige-izmedu-eintrachta-i-rangersa-nitko-ih-nije-ocekivao-a-sada-mogu-uci-u-povijest-5c63e514-d618-11ec-8ae4-6e7dc27df2db |access-date=19 May 2022|publisher=[[RTL Televizija]]|language=hr}}</ref> where they defeated [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] 5–4 on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 May 2022 |title=Kristijan Jakić postao 10. Hrvat koji je podigao pehar Europske lige |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/kristijan-jakic-postao-deseti-hrvat-koji-je-osvojio-europsku-ligu---724826.html |access-date=19 May 2022 |website=[[Dnevnik Nove TV]]|language=hr}}</ref>

On 29 May 2022, the transfer was made permanent and Jakić signed a four-year contract with Frankfurt.<ref>{{cite web|website=Eintracht Frankfurt|url=https://en.eintracht.de/news/jakic-bleibt-ueber-den-sommer-hinaus-142121|title=Jakic makes deal permanent|date=29 May 2022|access-date=22 July 2022}}</ref>

===FC Augsburg===
On 19 January 2024, Jakić moved to fellow Bundesliga club [[FC Augsburg]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2023–24 FC Augsburg season|2023–24 season]], with an option to buy if obligations were met.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Augsburg|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/article/fca-verstaerkt-sich-mit-kristijan-jaki-19439|title=FCA verstärkt sich mit Kristijan Jakić|trans-title=FCA strengthens with Kristijan Jakić|date=19 January 2024|access-date=20 January 2024|language=de}}</ref> On 24 May 2024, he signed for the club permanently on a four-year contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Augsburg|url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/fca-trigger-option-to-buy-kristijan-jaki-20220|title=FCA trigger option to buy Kristijan Jakić|date=24 May 2024|access-date=2 July 2024}}</ref>

== International career ==
Jakić received his first call-up to the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]] on 20 September 2021, when coach [[Zlatko Dalić]] called him up for the October [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] and [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Dalić objavio popis za nastavak kvalifikacija: Pozvao mladog asa iz Bayerna, vratio Brekala, nema Rebića i Petkovića! |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-objavio-popis-za-nastavak-kvalifikacija-za-svjetsko-prvenstvo-vatrene-cekaju-cipar-i-slovacka---667392.html |website=Gol.hr |access-date=26 June 2025|language=hr |date=20 September 2021}}</ref> He made his debut on 8 October against the former opponent, being replaced in the 84th minute; the match ended in a 3–0 victory for the Croats.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bradovski|first=Mihaela|date=8 October 2021|title=Debitant Jakić: 'Trenutno proživljavam svoje najbolje nogometne trenutke'|url=https://sportnet.rtl.hr/vijesti/555587/nogomet-reprezentacija/debitant-jakic-trenutno-prozivljavam-svoje-najbolje-nogometne-trenutke/|access-date=9 October 2021|website=RTL Croatia|language=hr|archive-date=2 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211102095529/https://sportnet.rtl.hr/vijesti/555587/nogomet-reprezentacija/debitant-jakic-trenutno-prozivljavam-svoje-najbolje-nogometne-trenutke/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

